main event: Two objects were sighted at Cambria AF Station, CA on August 19, 1957. One descended slowly while the other ascended and both faded out after 1-2 minutes. There was another report of three similar stacked objects.
interesting points: Sighting occurred at about 2030/0410Z,Lasted between 1-2 minutes, Objects were reported 5-10 miles and 1 mile apart, Former conclusions were that the objects were primarily balloons or aircraft (Jupiter), Reported similar objects were seen stacked.
witness description: No specific witnesses detailed, incidents reported through a record card.
